title: docs: Minor grammar fixes. Input needed on other proposed enhancements.
body:
I was lying in bed with a cold today and decided to do some doc cleanup.

There are a few other changes I would like to make but would like some input first:

1. The Unit Testing section of the guide is incomplete. I would be happy to finish it off if whoever wrote the original doc could give me a few lines of what they intended to cover under each incomplete heading.
2. The tutorial is using an older version of the seed project. What about updating it to use yeoman or at least Testacular? Not sure if that would make it harder for Windows users, though.
3. The tutorial is also using the "global function" style. What about updating it to use myApp.controller() as that seems to be a best practice?

title: fix($rootScope): allow removing a listener during event
body:
There is a bug, if an event listener is removed during the event. The next listener can be skipped, or null pointer exception can happen.

Not sure, what is the best solution for this problem.

I assume, that removing listeners does not happen so often. Otherwise we might iterate through the array and remove empty items after every event / or just sometimes :-D

feat(scenario):  add mouseover method to the ngScenario dsl
body:
so e2e tests are more readable.
- it adds a mouseover() method to element that trigger the mouseover
event on that element.

Motivation: I wanted to write a test that checks that the method in
the ng-mouseover directive was correct.

````coffeescript
it "should display the user friends when mouseover the avatar ", ->
  element(".user-avatar").mouseover()
  # ...
````

title: Add feature to use key for mapping in ngRepeat
body:
The attribute `npRepeatUseKey` toggles whether to use the key (for arrays,
this would be the index, for objects, this would be the key) for mapping
values to their respective scopes.

I have not added spec/tests and documentation changes because I'm awaiting input/feedback on this implementation.

Referring to Issue #1374

title: $http config.param expands array values properly.
body:
Today, calling e.g. $http(url, { params: { a: [1,2,3] } }) results in a query
string like "?a=%5B1%2C2%2C3%5D" which is undesirable. This commit enhances
buildURL to createa query string like "?a=1&a=2&a=3".

Fixes #1363.

title: chore(testing): Testacular config files + rake tasks
body:
- adds testacular config files for jqlite, jquery, modules and e2e tests
- replaces obsolete JsTD Rake tasks with Testacular onces
- rake tasks are parameterazied so that they can be used locally as well as on CI server

usage:

rake test  # run all tests on Chrome
rake test[Safari]  # run all tests on Safari
rake test:jqlite # run unit tests using jqlite on Chrome
rake test:jqlite[Safari,"--reporter=dots"]  # run jqlite-based unit tests on Safari with dots reporter
rake autotest:jquery  # start testacular with jquery-based config and watch fs for changes
rake test:e2e # run end to end tests
